Since your income won't be very high to start with, consider a roadside stand, or a booth at a flea market or community tag sale. {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/1/1f/Grow-Your-Own-Flowers-and-Sell-Them-Step-9Bullet1.jpg/v4-460px-Grow-Your-Own-Flowers-and-Sell-Them-Step-9Bullet1.jpg","bigUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/1/1f/Grow-Your-Own-Flowers-and-Sell-Them-Step-9Bullet1.jpg/v4-760px-Grow-Your-Own-Flowers-and-Sell-Them-Step-9Bullet1.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":325,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":536.5934065934066,"licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
</p><p><br />
</p></div>"}

If you live on a road where you get enough traffic to have the stand in your yard, consider leaving a few products out all the time, with an 'honors system' can for payment. Be sure to empty the can regularly, while most people are honest - some are not. {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/0/01/Grow-Your-Own-Flowers-and-Sell-Them-Step-9Bullet2.jpg/v4-460px-Grow-Your-Own-Flowers-and-Sell-Them-Step-9Bullet2.jpg","bigUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/0/01/Grow-Your-Own-Flowers-and-Sell-Them-Step-9Bullet2.jpg/v4-760px-Grow-Your-Own-Flowers-and-Sell-Them-Step-9Bullet2.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":325,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":536.5934065934066,"licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
</p><p><br />
</p></div>"}

Take pictures of your products and create posters to decorate your booth. {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/9/9a/Grow-Your-Own-Flowers-and-Sell-Them-Step-10Bullet1.jpg/v4-460px-Grow-Your-Own-Flowers-and-Sell-Them-Step-10Bullet1.jpg","bigUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/9/9a/Grow-Your-Own-Flowers-and-Sell-Them-Step-10Bullet1.jpg/v4-760px-Grow-Your-Own-Flowers-and-Sell-Them-Step-10Bullet1.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":325,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":536.5934065934066,"licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
</p><p><br />
</p></div>"}

Put signs at intersections near your home. Don't hang them on poles, and be sure they don't create a line-of-sight hazard. (Signs that do this are often removed, and you could get cited by the authorities for creating a hazard). {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/5/50/Grow-Your-Own-Flowers-and-Sell-Them-Step-10Bullet2.jpg/v4-460px-Grow-Your-Own-Flowers-and-Sell-Them-Step-10Bullet2.jpg","bigUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/5/50/Grow-Your-Own-Flowers-and-Sell-Them-Step-10Bullet2.jpg/v4-760px-Grow-Your-Own-Flowers-and-Sell-Them-Step-10Bullet2.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":325,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":536.5934065934066,"licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
